title: Foecke leads Nebraska to road sweep
text:
Foecke leads Nebraska to road sweep 
CHAMPAIGN, Ill. — When Mikaela Foecke’s serve literally brought a teammate to tears in practice last week, Nebraska volleyball coach John Cook decided it was time to let the freshman outside hitter do a little more serving in matches. 
By the time Foecke finished a dazzling run from the service stripe Saturday, No. 3 Nebraska was well on its way to a 25-22, 25-18, 25-19 road sweep of No. 16 Illinois, in which tough serving and rugged defense again was the formula for NU’s 13th win in 14 matches.     Subscription required
